name: kotlin-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for Kotlin programming in Android
globs: **/*.kt

- Use extension functions for clean code
- Implement functional programming patterns when appropriate
- Use proper scope functions (let, apply, run, with, also)
- Implement property delegation when necessary
- Use data classes for model objects
- Leverage Kotlin's type system
- Implement sealed classes for limiting type hierarchies
- Use destructuring declarations
- Avoid nullable types when possible
- Use null safety features correctly
- Implement infix functions for readable code
- Use operator overloading appropriately
- Implement proper error handling with Result type 